$interpreted: Yan-Bo: I figure this is all because of the rain lately.
Puggi: Oooh, this tree is real big~
Sharice: Has that voice been coming from here?
Yan-Bo: Indeed. Wind blowing through this tree and stone,
Yan-Bo: then throughout the valley. Created quite the racket, it has!
Sharice: Then what's up with them saying there's a monster that wants to eat them?
Horned Mandora: Huh!? Didn't you say the monster was angry and wanted to eat us?
Mandora: Not me! He said the monster was hungry, and that's why he got angry!
Spacy Mandora: I didn't say that! He's the one that said the monster sounded scary, so it must be hungry!
Spacy Mandora: Nuh uhh! He's the one who said the monster's voice was spooky!
Mandora: I didn't say it was a monster! I just said it sounded "like" a monster!
Spacy Mandora: ...eh?
Mandora King: Dora...
Puggi: I see...
Sharice: ......
Yan-Bo: Ah, so just a rumor, it was!
Yan-Bo: Hm... So many stones. A bit difficult, even for me.
Yan-Bo: Miss, would you come help an old man?
Sharice: Ah... alright, if it'll speed things up.
Puggi: These sprouts look pretty familiar...

Mandora King: Oh... ohhh...!
Are these our missing children? They disappeared days ago!
Sharice: These are Mandora children? You don't think...

Sharice: Could this tree be protecting the saplings? 
...Nah, that's impossible.
Yan-Bo: Nature works in mysterious ways, young lady!
Yan-Bo: And yet, this tree seems gravely injured. Rest, it must.
Puggi: ......

Mandora King: Thank you all so much for saving them, dora~!
You must have all been sent by the great hero!
Mandora: Doraâ€”Ora~
Sharice: What happened?
Sharice: Huh? What the heck are you doing?
Steel-Dora: Hmph, I was hoping to grab a few more while you lot were busy with the monster...
Sharice: I knew it! You're an imposter!
Puggi: Kids! Your dad is coming to save you!
Yan-Bo: Be careful! Do not hurt the Mandora!
Steel-Dora: He's right! Get close to me, I'll take care of this!
Sharice: Is everyone just going to stand by and watch him kidnap those Mandora?
Horned Mandora: Dora~~ Dora~~
Puggi: Kids...
???: Child...
Puggi: That voice...
???: Child, thank you... come to me... take my power...
Puggi: Whoever you are, Mandora Kingdom's peace...
Puggi: Is in the hands of the main character, now!
Sharice: Your wounds... was that from the tree, just now!?
Yan-Bo: Now's your chance!
Sherlock: Damn, I would have been rich! Aaaaghh!!
Puggi: Could this have been the voice I was hearing this whole time!?
Mandora King: Could it be that you're the one from legend? My grandpa's grandpa's grandpa's grandpa's...
Mandora King: The first king... the founder...!?
Mandora King: You've suffered such severe injuries for us!

Yan-Bo: Ah, this fake hero... read the elder scroll, he has.
I believe this scroll should remain in the kingdom.
Sharice: So Puggi wasn't hearing things? It was really this great hero calling him?
Yan-Bo: It truly seems that this hero has been watching over the kingdom.
Yan-Bo: The one everyone has been searching for. Under their noses the whole time, he has been.
Puggi: With the help of Miss Sharice and this old man, Puggi the main character saves the world once again!
Sharice: But you've still got that sprout on your head, birdbrain. You think it's alright to go back to Maple Lake like that?
Puggi: Back to Maple Lake? But... I belong here, don't I?
Mandora: Doradora~

Mandora Hero: Child, thank you for protecting this land.
However, you cannot stay here.

Puggi: Owowowow!!
Is it alright to just rip it out like that!?
Mandora King: Dora~ Doraaaa~
Puggi: Eh? I don't understand what they're saying?
Sharice: I can't believe we were so close to the valley. We must have done a lap around the whole kingdom!
Spear Mandora: Dora... Dora......
Sharice: Here... take my spear and armor. I have extras, anyway.
Sharice: Don't forget your training!
Spear Mandora: Dora! Dora!
Puggi: Children, I know you'll miss me, but... goodbyes were never supposed to be easy~

Puggi: My children!! Don't miss me too much!
...But don't forget about me, either!
Horned Mandora: Dora! Dora!!!
Puggi: I don't understand you guys anymore, but I know those are cries of sadness!
Yan-Bo: Dear friend, please take this bottle of wine. A gift.
Mandora King: Dora...
Yan-Bo: This is where we part ways. Yet, let us not part in sadness!
Mandora King: Dora~ Doraaaa~

Sharice: Yan-Bo, if this cave stays open like this...
What if more bad people come in? More people who want to harm the Mandora?
Sharice: I just bumped into another kid who was looking for them...
Yan-Bo: Hmm, yes. Maybe we should find a very large boulder...
Puggi: I remember this tree~ I was on a walk, and then I lost Pang, so I took a nap underneath it.
Yan-Bo: I guess the great hero was always here at this entrance, and he rushed over to help the Mandora.
Yan-Bo: But then he ran into trouble...
Sharice: You know, if we do this we won't be able to go visit the Mandora anymore, either.
Yan-Bo: Who knows! This time next year, perhaps Puggi's head will sprout once again!
Yan-Bo: Ahh, the winds of spring blow once again~
Yan-Bo: Let us return home! Pang and Hestia must be worried!
Puggi: That reminds me, where did Pang run off to...?
